<div class="listitem js-listitem"> <article class="production-viewing -viewing js-production-viewing" data-viewing-id="40806609" data-person="SilentDawn"> <a class="avatar -a40" href="/silentdawn/" > <img src="https://a.ltrbxd.com/resized/avatar/twitter/1/0/0/7/4/9/shard/http___pbs.twimg.com_profile_images_616321753703403520_3hNWu9ma-0-80-0-80-crop.jpg?v=45df9a7f52" alt="SilentDawn" width="40" height="40" /> </a> <div class="body"> <div class="attribution-block -large"> <div class="body"> <span class="attribution-detail"> <a href="/silentdawn/film/mulholland-drive/2/" class="context" title="Read SilentDawn’s review"> Review by <span class="owner"><strong class="displayname">SilentDawn</strong></span> </a> </span> <span class="content-reactions-strip -viewing"> <span class="rating -green rated-10"> ★★★★★ </span> <span class="inlineicon icon-16 -ignoreactionpseudo icon-liked -hidelabel"><span class="icon" role="presentation"></span><span class="label">Liked</span></span> <a href="/silentdawn/film/mulholland-drive/2/#comments" class="inlineicon icon-16 -ignoreactionpseudo icon-comment"><span class="icon" role="presentation"></span><span class="label">34</span></a> </span> </div> </div> <div class="js-review " > <div class="body-text -prose -reset js-review-body js-collapsible-text" data-full-text-url="/s/full-text/viewing:40806609/" data-is-translatable="true" lang="en" > <div class="collapsed-text"> <p><strong>100</strong></p><p>Sixteen Reasons why I love <em>Mulholland Drive: </em></p><p>1. The Jitterbug.<br />2. "Okay, Irene! Won't that be the day?" <br />3. "Napkin." <br />4. Billy Ray Cyrus. <br />5. The Cowboy. <br />6. David Lynch and his distorted view of American symbols - Hollywood auditions, diners, nightclubs, limos, and darkened hills. <br />7. The usage of the blue box as an existential portal for various detours and repetitions. <br />8. That camera push-in towards Betty as 'Sixteen Reasons' reaches its peak. Might as well be my favorite moment in all of cinema. <br />9. The refusal to tell conventional themes and popular history via typical narrative functions. <br />10. Lynch framing and elaborating on doubles and parallel universes without fully exploring or ruining the mystery of the similarities/differences.…</p> </div> </div> <div class="viewing-actions"> <div class="review-actions"> <p class="like-link-target react-component" data-component-class="LikeComponent" data-likeable-identifier='{"lid":"rCcD9","uid":"viewing:40806609","type":"viewing","typeName":"review"}' data-likeable="true" data-element-type="p" data-likes-page="/silentdawn/film/mulholland-drive/2/likes/" data-format="count" data-count="7253" data-owner="SilentDawn" > <span class="has-icon icon-16 icon-like"></span> </p> <button hidden class="translation-button button -text" data-translation-control-for="rCcD9"> <span class="label js-label">Translate</span> </button> <div hidden class="translation-disclaimer js-translation-disclaimer"> Translated from <span class="js-language-name"></span> by <span class="js-translated-by"></span> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </article> </div>
